item.title: CVE-2022-41274|2024-08-03T12:42:44.061Z -- sap -- disclosure%20management
item.description: SAP Disclosure Management - version 10.1, allows an authenticated attacker to exploit certain misconfigured application endpoints to read sensitive data. These endpoints are normally exposed over the network and successful exploitation can lead to the exposure of data like financial reports.
